Mathematical content:
The inverse of the Sp anti-equivalence is the 2^ functor restricted to Stone spaces.
On objects both functors are identity (both StoneCat and BooleωCat have objects = Booleω).
On morphisms, given f : Sp C → Sp B, the inverse functor produces the unique
BoolHom B C such that Sp(BoolHom) = f. This is exactly the 2^ action: precompose by f.

